p: The prevalence of group A was 51.7% (106/205) and group B 48.3% (99/205) . All the group A Kilifi sequences clustered within clade A2b (84/106, 79.2%) and within the unique clade A2c (22/106, 20.8%). No A1 or A2a sequences were observed. Within group B, 48.5% (48/99) of the sequences clustered within subgroup B1 and 51.5% (51/99) of the sequences clustered within subgroup B2.
